Merge pull request #6 from Mraoul/exceptions

Exceptions refactoring.
Added missing exception handling blocks
Updated tests to check for RuntimError instead of BadRarFile, this behavior should be closer to zipfile
Added missing exception handler

This is a work-around to a bug/flaw in unrar lib where it won't return an ERAR_MISSING_PASSWORD when attempting to extract a file that is password protected. Current behavior would return an empty string, new bavior raises an exception
If a rar file has an encrypted header, this will allow it to be opened and read/loaded

Modified how some calls to unrarlib are handled, mainly adding more exception handling. In certain places RuntimError is raised which is similar to how zipfile handles certain situations. Inability to extract password protected files, for example, raises a RuntimeError in zipfile.

Turned every ERAR code (except succes) into an exception based on the original UnrarException class which inherited from Exception.
Biggest change is that ERAR_ARCHIVE_END is also an exception and should be handled accordingly.
ERAR messages that were not necessarily errors (such as missing password) do not have the pythonic 'Error' designation and are named accordingly (e.g., MissingPassword)
Modified how _check_readheader_result and _check_process_result work. Now both function check every error case and only return on success (in every other case an exception is raised that must be handled. This fixes #3 which is caused by the unrarlib returning an error code that is not checked for (22 Missing Password while trying to process rar files that have headers encrypted) which causes rarfile to go into an infinite loop.
Added missing errors codes for completenes
Updated version for sphinx.
Updated unrar source dep.
Updated version.
